"2:185:37" : {s: 2, a: 185, w: 37, r: "عدد", t: "ٱلْعِدَّةَ", l: "عِدَّة", lc: 11, tl: "l-ʿidata", lb: "ইদ্দত, নির্দিষ্ট সময়",e: "the prescribed period", b: "সংখ্যা", i: "bilangan", f: 2, rm: "to count, number, reckon, make the census of. addun - number, computation, determined number. adadun - number. iddatun - a number, prescribed term, counting, to count, legal waiting period for a woman after she is divorced or becomes a widow before she may marry again. add - to prepare, make ready. addina - those who count. madudun - counted one."},
